    <stitle>DT/DTA-466 Diesel Engine Service (1990) - LUBRICATING OIL PUMP, OIL FILTERS AND COOLER - LUBRICATING OIL
        PUMP - REASSEMBLY
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="5">
        <title>REASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new crankshaft front oil seal into the lubricating oil pump housing as follows:
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Apply gasket eliminator #515 to the O.D. of the oil seal.</para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Press the seal into the oil pump housing so the front of the seal is flush with the
                    front of the oil pump housing. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150920">9.20</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef4150919" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12276" filename="../figcg1/cg12276.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.19. Check Housing to Rotor Clearance (Method One).</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef4150920" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="cg12277" filename="../figcg1/cg12277.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 9.20. Oil Seal Installation Diagram.</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install a new oil pump housing ring into the front cover, then install the housing plate.
                Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150921">9.21</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the inner rotor onto the gear spline. With the inner rotor installed, tap in the
                crankshaft key with a plastic hammer. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150922">9.22</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble a new O-Ring and the outer rotor into the housing. Lubricate the rotator with clean
                engine oil. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef4150923">9.23</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
            <figure id="ef4150921" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12278" filename="../figcg1/cg12278.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.21. Install Ring and Plate.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150922" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12279" filename="../figcg1/cg12279.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.22. Install Inner Rotor and Crankshaft Key.</caption>
            </figure>
            <figure id="ef4150923" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="cg12280" filename="../figcg1/cg12280.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 9.23. Assemble Housing Components.</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the outer rotor and housing over the inner rotor. Align the bolt holes and install
                the "patch" bolts. Tighten the bolts to the standard torque. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e415_195.xml" xrefid="ef4150924">9.24</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
                <emph type="bold"></emph>
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>"Patch" bolts must be used to prevent leakage.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the vibration damper as specified in
                <hotlnk document="e415_E41507.xml" xrefid="e41507">VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL
                    AND CRANKCASE</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
